comment_data.body:
reluctant to introduce a new module for every lsp feature.  (maybe i'm wrong though)

lsp already has a way to enable capabilities, can we just document how to use it? 

```
  vim.lsp.config('*', {
    capabilities = {
      ...
    },
  })
```

I see that `setup_autocmds` is called by `enable()`. is this something users want to dynamically toggle ?

```suggestion
  vim.lsp.buf_request(bufnr, method, function(client)
    return vim.lsp.util.make_position_params(win, client.offset_encoding)
  end, function(...)
    self:handler(...)
  end)
```

comment_regular_data.body:
I've migrated to an OOP style approach similar to the one in the semantic tokens handler, let me know what you think (cc @ofseed). I can't figure out how to disable linked editing with `lsp.config` yet; I tried this:

```lua
vim.lsp.config('*', {
  capabilities = {
    textDocument = {
      linkedEditingRange = false,
    },
  },
})
```

but it still seems to perform linked editing...
